<h3> Q: What happens if I check off lots of boxes for the first question?</h3>

 A: The more categories you check off, the more types of people you
 meet. Even if you check off all ten rows, most of your dates
 will only fit one or two categories.

<h3>
 Q: Why doesn't the second column just say "check off what you are"?
</h3>
 A: It used to, and that is still what most people do. This
 wording is an expansion of that: you may want dates who are
 genderqueer-friendly whether or not you identify that way. You may want
 dates who are both man-friendly and woman-friendly (i.e. "bisexual")
 even if you yourself aren't both a man and a woman.


